OL,7,FThe former England boss is in his
OL,8,Fsecond spell in charge of the south
OL,9,FLondon club, having returned for the
OL,10,Ffinal 10 games of last season when he
OL,11,Fsigned a short-term deal to take over
OL,12,Ffrom the sacked Patrick Vieira.
OL,14,FHe guided the club to an 11th-placed
OL,15,Ffinish before agreeing to continue as
OL,16,Fmanager for the 2023-24 campaign.
